<div id="descriptionContainer">
  
      <div id="description" class="readable stacked" style="right:0">
        
<span id="freeTextContainer15519544041930589972">In &quot;The Day of the Scorpion,&quot; Scott draws us deeper in to his epic of India at the close of World War II. With force and subtlety, he recreates both private ambition and perversity, and the politics of an entire subcontinent at a turning point in history. <br/><br/>As the scorpion, encircled by a ring of fire, will sting itself to death, so does the British raj hasten its own destru</span>
  <span id="freeText15519544041930589972" style="display:none">In "The Day of the Scorpion," Scott draws us deeper in to his epic of India at the close of World War II. With force and subtlety, he recreates both private ambition and perversity, and the politics of an entire subcontinent at a turning point in history. <br /><br />As the scorpion, encircled by a ring of fire, will sting itself to death, so does the British raj hasten its own destruction when threatened by the flames of Indian independence. Brutal repression and imprisonment of India's leaders cannot still the cry for home rule. And in the midst of chaos, the English Laytons withdraw from a world they no longer know to seek solace in denial, drink, and madness.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="15519544041930589972" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

      </div>
