<div id="review_2835163964" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2835163964" />
    <a title="Rebecca" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/70058633-rebecca"><img alt="Rebecca" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2835163964?book_show_action=true">May 30, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rebecca" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rebecca" href="/user/show/70058633-rebecca">Rebecca</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780099478829" href="/book/show/414828.The_Day_of_the_Scorpion">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/70058633-rebecca?shelf=uk">uk</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/70058633-rebecca?shelf=india">india</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2835163964" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4674017080723696449">I read The Jewel in the Crown a few years ago and was completely bowled over by how unexpectedly brilliant it was. I remembered it as the 1980s mini-series although I don’t actually remember very much from that apart from the character Merrick and the fact that it was a real television event that everyone was watching and talking about. In the years since I don’t remember the original books or Paul Scott being discussed at all so I have no idea why I decided to buy the book in the first instance</span>
  <span id="freeText4674017080723696449" style="display:none">I read The Jewel in the Crown a few years ago and was completely bowled over by how unexpectedly brilliant it was. I remembered it as the 1980s mini-series although I don’t actually remember very much from that apart from the character Merrick and the fact that it was a real television event that everyone was watching and talking about. In the years since I don’t remember the original books or Paul Scott being discussed at all so I have no idea why I decided to buy the book in the first instance, but I do know that it sat on my shelf for years before I got around to reading it. I think I was expecting some sort of end-of-empire soap opera...<br /><br />It has taken me so long to read the second in the series because now I’m worried about reading them all too quickly and not having the next instalments to look forward to in the future. It did mean that I took some time to get reacquainted with the story, but once again, it did not disappoint. Granted sometimes Scott’s writing is extremely detailed, especially in relation to political discourse and that may not be for everyone, but alongside this is his ability to write believably in multiple voices, his knowledge of the place and time and ability to write so evocatively about it, the way he looks at the bigger picture and then straight afterwards hones in on the ‘small’ and ‘personal’ with real understanding and, when needed, warmth and compassion. <br /><br />There is just so much to this, with a storyline that is so complex and yet so nuanced, that there is no way that I can do it credit. I really don’t understand why Scott seems to have fallen out of fashion as a writer. Highly recommended.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4674017080723696449" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


